\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
1.
 Purpose
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
This policy establishes mandatory controls for maintaining the integrity of Elko County information systems and for protecting those systems from malicious code,
 exploitation,
 and unauthorized changes.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
2.
 Scope
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
This policy applies to all Elko County Information Operations (ECIO) personnel,
 County employees,
 elected officials,
 contractors,
 vendors,
 and any other individuals or services accessing County information systems.
 Technical implementation requirements apply to all information systems,
 networks,
 endpoints,
 and supporting infrastructure owned,
 leased,
 managed,
 or operated by Elko County,
 including all systems that process,
 store,
 or transmit Criminal Justice Information (CJI).
\end_layout

