\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
6.
 Policy Statement
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.1 Malicious Code Protection
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The Systems Administrator shall implement malicious code protection mechanisms at system entry and exit points and on all workstations,
 servers,
 and mobile devices to detect and eradicate malicious code.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Automatic Updates
\series default
:
 The Systems Administrator shall configure malicious code protection mechanisms to perform automatic updates of virus definitions and scanning engines every twenty-four (24) hours.
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Exception
\series default
:
 Where a system does not support automatic updates,
 the Systems Administrator shall perform manual updates every twenty-four (24) hours.
\end_layout

\end_deeper

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Real-Time Scanning
\series default
:
 The Systems Administrator shall configure malicious code protection mechanisms to perform real-time scanning of files from external sources as files are downloaded,
 opened,
 or executed.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Periodic Scanning
\series default
:
 The Systems Administrator shall configure malicious code protection mechanisms to perform full system scans every twenty-four (24) hours.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Response Actions
\series default
:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The Systems Administrator shall configure malicious code protection mechanisms to automatically block or quarantine detected malicious code.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The Systems Administrator shall configure malicious code protection mechanisms to automatically alert the Systems Administrator and the Assistant IT Director upon detection of malicious code.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The Systems Administrator shall review false positives generated by malicious code protection mechanisms prior to releasing quarantined files.
\end_layout

\end_deeper

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.2 System Monitoring
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Monitoring Tools
\series default
:
 The Network Administrator shall employ automated monitoring tools (e.g.,
 IDS/IPS,
 SIEM) to monitor inbound and outbound communications traffic for unusual or unauthorized activity.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Perimeter Monitoring
\series default
:
 The Network Administrator shall configure monitoring to check for indicators of attacks and unauthorized connections at external boundaries and at key internal boundaries.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Command-and-Control Detection
\series default
:
 The Network Administrator shall use system monitoring tools to inspect network flow and Domain Name System (DNS) logs for traffic patterns indicative of malware command-and-control (C2) activity.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Alerting
\series default
:
 The Systems Administrator and Network Administrator shall analyze and respond to system-generated security alerts.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Incident Escalation
\series default
:
 The Systems Administrator and Network Administrator shall escalate alerts assessed as potential incidents through the operational incident management process under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.06"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.3 Information Integrity and Input Validation
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Integrity Checks
\series default
:
 The Systems Administrator shall employ integrity verification tools (e.g.,
 File Integrity Monitoring) to detect unauthorized changes to software,
 firmware,
 and information.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
CJI Integrity Verification
\series default
:
 For systems processing CJI,
 the Systems Administrator shall perform integrity checks every seven (7) calendar days.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Input Validation
\series default
:
 The Systems Administrator shall verify that information systems acquired or operated by the Department implement input validation controls (e.g.,
 character set,
 length,
 numerical range,
 format) sufficient to prevent injection attacks and data corruption.
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Exception
\series default
:
 For vendor-managed systems where input validation is implemented by the software vendor,
 the Systems Administrator shall confirm the control during procurement review under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.13"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Supply Chain Risk Management (SCRM) and Vendor Governance Policy) and during secure software lifecycle review under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:2.15"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (System Development and Secure Software Lifecycle Policy).
\end_layout

\end_deeper

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Spam Protection
\series default
:
 The Systems Administrator shall employ spam protection mechanisms at information system entry and exit points.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Spam Protection Updates
\series default
:
 The Systems Administrator shall configure spam protection signatures to update automatically every twenty-four (24) hours.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.4 Flaw Remediation
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The Systems Administrator shall remediate information system flaws in accordance with 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:2.09"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.5 Memory Protection
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The Systems Administrator shall configure operating systems and applications to utilize memory protection controls (e.g.,
 Data Execution Prevention,
 Address Space Layout Randomization) to prevent the execution of unauthorized code.
\end_layout

